 ### Multi-local design
 One service instance serves multiple stores simultaneously. Every operation carries `storeId` as mandatory context:
-- **Pub/Sub messages**: body is plain text GCS path `{storeId}/{filename}` — `storeId` is the prefix before the first `/`
-- **GCS paths**: always `{bucket}/{storeId}/{filename}`
-- **HTTP to Central**: `codLocal` (storeId) always included in the request body
+- **Pub/Sub messages (TC-02)**: body is the full GCS blob name `CIERREDIA/{storeCode}/TRANSFERIR/{filename}.zip` — `storeCode` is the **second** path segment
+- **GCS paths (TC-02)**: `CIERREDIA/{storeCode}/TRANSFERIR/{filename}.zip` (input) → `CIERREDIA/{storeCode}/PROCESADO/{filename}.zip` (after HTTP OK)
+- **HTTP to Central**: `codLocal` (storeCode) always included in the request body
 
 ### Pub/Sub subscription API
 `jlib-pubsub` does not expose `@PubSubMessageHandler`. The real API is `IMessageSubscriber`, which at runtime is decorated by `jlib-pubsub-logging` with MDC context. Subscriptions are registered in `@PostConstruct` via `messageSubscriber.startListening()`. The handler returns `CompletableFuture<Boolean>`: `true` = ACK, `false` = NACK (triggers retry).
 
 ### GCS move operation
-GCS has no native rename/move. `GcsStorageAdapter.moveBlob()` is implemented as: download → upload to target path → delete source. This is used by TC-02 to move processed blobs to `{storeId}/procesado/`.
-
-### KMS pattern
-`jlib-kms` is a transitive dependency of `jlib-secretmanager`. In `application-local.yml`, `KmsAutoConfiguration` is excluded and `app.gcp.kms.enabled: false`. When KMS adapters are implemented, they must use `@ConditionalOnProperty(name = "app.gcp.kms.enabled", havingValue = "true")` for the real adapter and `havingValue = "false", matchIfMissing = true` for the no-op.
+GCS has no native rename/move. `GcsStorageAdapter.moveBlob()` is implemented as: download → upload to target path → delete source. This is used by TC-02 to move processed blobs. The replacement uses configurable folder names from `GcsStorageProperties`: `.replace("/" + gcsProperties.transferFolder() + "/", "/" + gcsProperties.processedFolder() + "/")`.
+
+### GCS single-bucket design
+One bucket (`GCS_BUCKET`) is shared across all use cases, differentiated by path prefix:
+- TC-02: `{closingDayPath}/{storeCode}/{transferFolder}/` → `{closingDayPath}/{storeCode}/{processedFolder}/`
+- TC-03: `{journalPath}/{storeCode}/{file}` (deleted after sending)
+- TC-04: `{clientReplicationPath}/{storeCode}/{processedFolder}/{file}`
+
+All path segments are configurable via `app.gcp.storage.*` with sensible defaults (`CIERREDIA`, `JOURNAL`, `REPLICA_CLIENTE`, `TRANSFERIR`, `PROCESADO`, `ERROR`).
+
+### Store registry
+`StoreRegistry` loads active multi-local stores from `SAADMIN.MN_TIENDA` at startup via `JpaStoreRepository.findByIndActivoAndMultiLocal(1, 1)`. Store codes are formatted as 3-digit zero-padded strings (`String.format("%03d", desClave)`). Used only by `ReplicationClientSchedulerAdapter` (TC-04); if the DB is unavailable at startup, the registry starts empty and logs a warning — the service continues running.
 
 ### HTTP to Central
-`CentralEndpointAdapter` uses Spring WebFlux `WebClient` directly — **not** `jlib-apicalls` — because the Central El Rosado legacy API does not support JWT. Calls block with `.block()` which is safe on Virtual Threads. Three endpoints:
-- `POST {url}/transaction/receive/file` — multipart, sends ZIP (TC-02, TC-03)
-- `POST {url}/transaction/send/name/file` — JSON, lists available replication files (TC-04)
-- `POST {url}/transaction/send/file` — JSON, downloads a replication file as Base64 (TC-04)
+`CentralEndpointAdapter` uses a `WebClient` bean pre-configured in `CentralWebClientConfig` (base URL + Reactor Netty timeout from `CentralProperties`). Not `jlib-apicalls` — Central is a legacy API without JWT. Calls block with `.block()` safe on Virtual Threads. Three endpoints:
+- `POST /transaction/receive/file` — multipart, sends ZIP (TC-02 type=`CIERREDIA`, TC-03 type=`JOURNAL`)
+- `POST /transaction/send/name/file` — JSON, lists replication files (TC-04 type=`REPLICA_CLIENTE`)
+- `POST /transaction/send/file` — JSON, downloads a replication file as Base64 (TC-04)
+
+The type values (`CIERREDIA`, `JOURNAL`, `REPLICA_CLIENTE`) are defined by the legacy Central API contract and configured via `app.central.file-types.*`.
 
